  "key_design_notes": [
    "JdbcConnection is a central hub — not thread-safe; stateful with a single volatile Connection",
    "ConnectionFactory (inner) is separate from outer ConnectionFactory<T>: inner one builds java.sql.Connection; outer one builds JdbcConnection subclasses",
    "ConnectionFactoryDecorator allows runtime-pluggable factory via JdbcConfiguration.CONNECTION_FACTORY_CLASS",
    "CancellableResultSet uses Decorator pattern; key optimization is cancel-before-close for un-exhausted result sets (e.g., snapshot table scans)",
    "Statement cache (BoundedConcurrentHashMap, 10k entries, LIRS eviction) reduces PreparedStatement creation overhead",
    "JdbcValueConverters is designed for subclassing by DB-specific connectors (MySQL, PostgreSQL, Oracle, etc.)",
    "TemporalPrecisionMode controls date/time schema shape: ADAPTIVE (DB precision), ISOSTRING, CONNECT (ms), MICROSECONDS, NANOSECONDS",
    "DefaultMainConnectionProvidingConnectionFactory creates main connection eagerly; used in parallel snapshot",
    "ResultReceiver + ValueConversionCallback pattern separates 'null value' from 'unsupported type' in column converters"
  ],

